>>8f476bc5-ed1f-4709-9bd1-2ea6cd8158dc
Yeah, that would be a nice feature. The external program you're talking about already exists in the form of a deduplicating filesystem, but they're intended for enterprise and not end users, so it's a pain in the ass to maintain, doesn't work on every OS, and consumes a lot of memory.

>>a43da966-678e-400e-aa5c-7c55a287e5b4
Low life means you don't have time to worry about interior design because you're too worried about either stealing enough shit to buy the basic necessities of life, being caught by the police, not being killed by some gangsters for selling drugs in their turf, or just because you're high all the time on whatever recreational drug of your choosing.
Which is funny, because it makes "cyberpunk" (at least as seen ITT and in the old 8ch board) just another edgy teenage subculture not unlike emos, goths and the like, pretending to be "low life" while coming from middle class families and making enough money to live in a nice apartment in the middle of a big city, buy the last computer gadgets and having the luxury of pick and choosing what furniture to buy to match with their "dystopian style", just because (at most) they explore abandoned factories once in a while and know enough about computers to write a basic python script.
